	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65287343"><p><div class="quote"><p>What happens to the kinetic energy of the astronaut who is instantly transported to another point in space?</p></div><p>The original post was intended to be funny, of course. But, taking your question as if the post were serious: </p><p>Quantum teleportation teleports only the quantum state of the particles, not the actual atoms themselves. To reassemble the object being "teleported," you would have to gather the required particles together, and use the information sent that allows you to know the quantum states to put each of the particles into the appropriate quantum state.</p><p>The quantum state of the original object is decohered in<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

